<h2>Travel by air</h2>
<p><strong>Fly Direct From 20 UK Airports</strong></p>
<p>Our range of UK airports helps keep your journey times to a minimum, and for your added convenience, we can also arrange your airport car-parking or an overnight airport hotel for you in advance – see details below.</p>
<p> </p>
<p><strong>Connecting Flights Via Europe</strong></p>
<p>Inghams has negotiated special rates to selected destinations with the following European airlines:</p>
<ul>
<li>K.L.M. via Amsterdam</li>
<li>S.A.S. via Copenhagen/Oslo</li>
</ul>
<p> </p>
<p>Flight details and full flight times will be given at the time of booking. You have a short flight from your UK airport to Amsterdam/Copenhagen/Oslo where you change aircraft before flying to your chosen destination. Your luggage is checked through to your final destination (except in Oslo, where you will have to reclaim your baggage).</p>
<p> </p>
<p><strong>British Airways via Gatwick/Heathrow</strong></p>
<p>For a £75 supplement we can offer connecting flights to airports shown in the table above from: Aberdeen, Belfast, Edinburgh, Glasgow, Jersey, Leeds-Bradford, Manchester and Newcastle. We recommend you book early in order to get the lowest tour operator economy booking class from Gatwick or Heathrow</p>
<p> </p>
<p><strong>"Scheduled/Low Cost" Carriers</strong></p>
<p>Low cost airlines do not offer meals and drinks though sometimes these can be purchased on board. Flight baggage allowance is one piece of luggage at 20kg on Easyjet, flybe, Jet2, Monarch, Norwegian and Thomson Airways. Ryanair is one piece of luggage at 15kg per person.</p>
<p> </p>
<p><strong>“No-Frills” Carriers</strong></p>
<p>No-frills airlines do not offer meals and drinks though sometimes these can be purchased on board. Flight baggage allowance is one piece of luggage at 20kg on Easyjet, flybe, Jet2, Monarch and Thomson Airways. Ryanair is one piece of luggage at 15kg per person.</p>
<div class="hr hr-spaced"></div>
<h2>Meals</h2>
<p>Complimentary food and beverages are continuously being reviewed by airlines and may no longer be offered free to economy class and charter flight passengers. All of our charter airlines (with the exception of Austrian Airlines) offer a ‘buy on board’ meal service.</p>
<div class="hr hr-spaced"></div>
<h2>Baggage Allowances</h2>
<p>All European flights (charter and scheduled), now limit each passenger to one item of checked in luggage weighing either 18 or 20kg. Exact details will be on your e-ticket</p>
<div class="hr hr-spaced"></div>
<h2>Pre-Bookable Seating Arrangements</h2>
<p>To ensure your party sits together, you can pre-book seats on the following airlines: Austrian Airlines and Thomson Airways (Innsbruck, Salzburg and Verona only).</p>
<p> </p>
<p>Simply reserve your seats at the time of booking up to 12 days before departure for a small charge of £9 per person return. Please note that seats may be separated by an aisle due to aircraft configurations. Exact seat numbers are given at check in. Should we cancel or change your airline to one that is not part of this scheme, we will issue a full refund.</p>
<div class="hr hr-spaced"></div>
<h2>UK Airport Car Parking</h2>
<p><strong>3 Great Offers For Your Convenience</strong></p>
<ol>
<li>Up to <strong>35% discount</strong> at all UK Airports</li>
<li>Special Airport Hotel Offers from only £35 per person! Including FREE PARKING</li>
<li>Meet and Greet valet parking at airports from only £45</li>
</ol>
<p> </p>
<p>Valet parking is ideal. Simply drive to the airport terminal where an APH representative meets you and takes your car to their nearby secure car park. On your return, your car is then delivered back to you directly at the terminal for you to drive straight off home.</p>
<p> </p>
<p>For full details and to book online go to <a rel="noopener noreferrer" href="http://www.aph.com/" target="_blank">www.aph.com/inghams</a></p>
<div class="hr hr-spaced"></div>
