<p>*This includes Standard Premier Class travel from London to Paris (with meals and drinks included) and a 6-berth shared couchette to Breschia. Travel from Breschia to Desenzano or Peschiera is in standard class. Upgrades on the overnight service to Breschia may be available within 3 months of departure, subject to availability. Please call our reservations team for details.</p>
<p> </p>
<p><strong>Upgrade:</strong> This includes meals and drinks on Eurostar, and a six-berth shared couchette to Brescia. Travel from Brescia to Desenzano or Peschiera is in standard class. Upgrades on the overnight service may be available within three months of departure date subject to availability and confirmation.</p>
<p>Please note that departures from Ebbsfleet or Ashford will involve different UK departure and arrival times.<br />Upgrades to Standard Premier Class available</p>
<p><a name="selfdrive"></a><strong>Self Drive</strong></p>
<p><strong>Driving to your holiday destination from the UK can be a convenient way to travel at your own pace.  We offer our holidays with return ferry or Eurotunnel Channel crossings instead of flights for a reduced price  All we ask is you arrive and depart your accommodation the same date as you flight arrivals.</strong> </p>
<p>To book, select your accommodation, and either a P&amp;O Ferries or Eurotunnel crossing, then call our reservations team for a quote.</p>
<p><strong><strong>Car Reductions</strong></strong></p>
<p>To calculate the price of your self-drive holiday, simply take the price of a holiday by air and deduct <strong>£150</strong> per person (£85 per person if travelling to Switzerland).</p>
<p><strong><strong>P&amp;O Ferries</strong></strong></p>
<p>You can choose one of the following routes:-</p>
<p>• <strong>Dover to Calais</strong>: Six Super-ferries operate the 75 minute crossing. You can upgrade to P&amp;O Ferries’ Club Plus service for just <strong>£13</strong> per person each way plus <strong>£7</strong> per car each way. This allows you access to the exclusive Club Lounge with complimentary tea, coffee, soft drinks, newspapers, waiter service and snack menu and priority boarding and disembarkation. If you prefer you can upgrade separately; Club Lounge <strong>£13</strong> per person each way, Priority Boarding <strong>£13</strong> per car each way.<br />Children aged 5-11 yrs eat <strong>FREE</strong> on P&amp;O Services!</p>
<p>• <strong>Hull to Zeebrugge</strong> <strong>or Rotterdam</strong>: A daily overnight service, ideal for travelling to Eastern Switzerland or Austria. Cabin accommodation is compulsory and available from <strong>£70</strong> each way for a 2-berth inside cabin. Meals are not included, but can be pre-booked. Priority boarding can be pre-booked for a supplement of <strong>£13</strong> per car each way.</p>
<p><strong>Eurotunnel</strong></p>
<p>Eurotunnel runs up to three services an hour during peak periods between Folkstone and Calais and offers the quickest method of taking your car across the channel. The journey takes just 35 minutes platform to platform. Please note: Eurotunnel does not accept LPG/Dual powered vehicles. If your vehicle is over 1.85m in height, high space must be reserved.<br />You can choose to <strong>upgrade your travel to Eurotunnel </strong>at a cost of <strong>£29</strong> per car. You can also upgrade your Eurotunnel crossing to ‘Flexi-Plus’ (not applicable for vehicles over 1.85m in height) for <strong>£99</strong> which includes dedicated check-in and priority boarding lanes, use of the exclusive Flexi-Plus lounge serving complimentary non-alcoholic drinks and snacks and the flexibility to take another departure if you arrive early, or late, at the terminal (change directly with Eurotunnel at the port).</p>
<p><strong>Important Information</strong></p>
<p>• You may travel on different outward and return routes, but both journeys must be with the same company. All cars on one booking must travel on the same crossings.</p>
<p>• Whilst every effort is made to arrange the dates and timings you request, services can book up quickly at busy times and in peak periods. As all cross-channel bookings are subject to availability, we will book the nearest possible alternative and confirm the details on your invoice.</p>
<p>• An administration fee is payable if you change any details of your crossings after you have made your booking</p>
<p>• Prices shown are for cars only, although people carriers and campervans may be booked with Eurotunnel for further supplements. We regret we cannot accept commercial vehicles or vehicles seating more than 9 people.</p>
<p>• The price that appears on our reservations system when you provisionally book your holiday may not include all route or accommodation supplements.</p>
<p>• Details of over-height vehicles, trailers, roof-racks, etc must be given at time of booking. Some restrictions/supplements may apply for vehicles over 1.85m.<br />Please consult P&amp;O Ferries or Eurotunnel’s websites for the most up-to-date information</p>
<p> </p>
<p> </p>
<p><strong>Eurotunnel</strong></p>
<p>Eurotunnel runs up to three services an hour during peak periods between <strong>Folkestone and Calais</strong>, and the journey takes just 35 minutes platform to platform. Upgrades to Eurotunnel are available ata cost of £50 per car. Please note that Eurotunnel does not accept LPG/Dual powered vehicles.</p>
<p> </p>
<p><strong><span class="accommodationname">How to book</span></strong></p>
<p>Any resort in a country featured in the Car Holiday Reductions box below can be booked as a car holiday. You must arrive and depart your resort on the same day as our flight days for that resort. We will require details of your intended dates and times of travel together with details of your car. Please advise us at the time of booking of the height and length of your vehicle so that the right space can be booked. Some routes carry a per person supplement.</p>
<p><strong><span class="accommodationname">What’s included</span></strong></p>
<p>• Folkestone to Calais by Eurotunnel (see table for supps).<br />• Resort accommodation and meal arrangements as confirmed.<br />• Services of our representatives and local agents.</p>
<p><strong><span class="accommodationname">What’s not included</span></strong></p>
<p>• Cross Channel supplements (see tables above).<br />• Seat/cabin supplements (details on request).<br />• Personal Insurance (see below) and Car Insurance<br />• En-route accommodation, meals, petrol, motorway charges, local fjord ferry crossings etc.<br />• Swiss Half-price Card if travelling to Switzerland.</p>
<p> </p>
<p><strong>Important Information</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>You may travel on different outward and return routes, but both journeys must be with the same company. All cars on one booking must travel on the same crossings.</li>
<li>Whilst every effort is made to arrange the dates and timings you request, services can book up quickly at busy times and in peak periods. As all cross channel bookings are subject to availability, we will book the nearest possible alternative and confirm details on your invoice.</li>
<li>An administration fee is payable if you change any details of your crossing after you have made your booking (see Booking Conditions)</li>
<li>Prices shown are for cars only, though minibuses and campervans may be booked with Eurotunnel for further supplements. We regret we cannot accept commercial vehicles seating more than 9 people.</li>
<li>The price that appears on our reservations system when you provisionally book your holiday may not include all route or accommodation supplements.</li>
<li>Details of overheight vehicles, trailers, roof racks, etc. must be given at the time of booking. Some restrictions may apply for vehicles over 1.85m</li>
</ul>
<p>We recommend that you consult the ferry companies' or Eurotunnel's website for the most up-to-date timetable information.</p>
<p> </p>
